reviewText: "Star-studded" is a term that gets tossed around casually, often without cause. Saying that the COMEDY 10 MOVIE PACK is star-studded is no exaggeration, however. Some of the most famous mid-20th century Hollywood actors appear in  these films. To name just a few: Bob Hope, Fred Astaire, Jimmy Stewart, Humphrey Bogart, Kirk Douglas and Jimmy Cagney. Not a bad list, huh?All of these public domain comedies are quite good. Transfer quality is fine, and the price a real bargain. With clean humor, sure-fire laughs and the best of performers, this is a collection that belongs in all home cinematic libraries.Another related DVD box set is theCOMEDY CLASSICS 50 MOVIE PACK COLLECTION. It contains six of these, plus such family favorites as the East Side Kids, Laurel & Hardy, Mickey Rooney and the Keystone Cops..The following alphabetized program list provides 1 to 10 viewer poll ratings for each title, plus their years of release and most prominent actors.(6.2) The Amazing Quest Of Ernest Bliss (1936) - Cary Grant(6.5) Beat The Devil (1953) - Humphrey Bogart/Gina Lollobrigida(8.0) His Girl Friday (1940) - Cary Grant/Rosalind Russell(6.4) Made For Each Other (1939) - Carole Lombard/James Stewart(5.5) The Medicine Man (1930) - Jack Benny(5.8) My Dear Secretary (1949) - Laraine Day/Kirk Douglas/Keenan Wynn/Rudy Vallee(6.9) My Favorite Brunette (1947) - Bob Hope/Dorothy Lamour/Peter Lorre/Lon Chaney Jr.(5.8) Pot o' Gold (1941) - James Stewart/Paulette Goddard(6.6) Royal Wedding (1951) - Fred Astaire/Jane Powell/Peter Lawford/Keenan Wynn(6.3) Something To Sing About (1937) - James Cagney/William Frawley

reviewText: .....UNLESS YOU JUST LIKE WATCHING REALLY OLD AND OBSCURE MOVIES ...then avoid this turkey.  This pack of dung is a shining example of why movie packs should be avoided ...they are just dumping grounds of unsellable movies......Of the ten movies in the pack the only one that was worth watching was My Favorite Brunette with Bob Hope and Dorothy Lamour ...it was typical Bob Hope fare and should satisfy his fans and a young Dorothy Lamour is always worth watching.

reviewText: 1. The Medicine ManDr. John Harvey falls for the delectable Mamie Goltz, whose life is controlled and made miserable by her overbearing tyrant of a father.Star: Jack Benny2. The Amazing AdventureA rich young man living the idyllic life of a lotus eater, is swimming in depression and fails to see it as a consequence of his empty life.  His physician challenges him to make his way in the world for twelve months without utilizing his wealth.Star: Gary Grant3. My Favorite BrunetteBaby photographer Ronnie Jackson, from his cell on death row in San Quentin, tells newsmen the story of his unlikely route to misery.Star: Bob Hope5. Something to Sing AboutA New York band leader and his wife head for Hollywood when he's offered a film contract.Star: James Cagney6. My Dear SecretaryA bestselling novelist recruits an aspiring female writer to become his secretary.
